---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Cloudflare Ray-ID Extract - GigaSieve Recipe" description="Extract and trace Cloudflare Ray-IDs from your logs for request debugging.">
    <section class="container mx-auto px-4 py-12 max-w-3xl">
        <nav class="text-sm text-slate-500 mb-6">
            <a href="/recipes" class="hover:text-emerald-400">Recipes</a>
            <span class="mx-2">/</span>
            <span class="text-slate-400">Cloudflare Ray-ID</span>
        </nav>

        <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-slate-200 mb-4">Cloudflare Ray-ID Extract</h1>
        <p class="text-slate-400 mb-8">
            Every Cloudflare request has a unique Ray-ID. Use this recipe to extract and search Ray-IDs 
            from your access logs for debugging specific requests.
        </p>

        <a href="/app" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-500 to-cyan-500 text-white font-bold py-3 px-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg mb-8">
            Open in App ->
        </a>

        <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 p-6 mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-300 mb-4">What is a Ray-ID?</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm mb-4">
                Cloudflare assigns a unique identifier (Ray-ID) to every HTTP request that passes through their network. 
                This ID appears in response headers and can be logged by your origin server.
            </p>
            <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm">
                Format: <code class="bg-slate-800 px-2 py-1 rounded">ray-[hex]-[datacenter]</code> (e.g., <code class="bg-slate-800 px-2 py-1 rounded">ray-7a1b2c3d4e5f-IAD</code>)
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 p-6 mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-300 mb-4">How to use</h2>
            <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-400 text-sm">
                <li>Open your access log in GigaSieve</li>
                <li>Use the filter: <code class="bg-slate-800 px-2 py-1 rounded">ray-</code></li>
                <li>Lines containing Ray-IDs will appear</li>
                <li>Copy the Ray-ID and search Cloudflare dashboard for details</li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-300 mb-4">Related</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <a href="/recipes/logs/nginx-status-codes" class="bg-slate-900 hover:bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-4 border border-slate-800">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-300">nginx Status Codes</h3>
            </a>
            <a href="/recipes/logs/top-ips" class="bg-slate-900 hover:bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-4 border border-slate-800">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-300">Top IPs</h3>
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>
